issue.title: Unit of measurement missing in entity options
issue.body:
### Checklist

- [X] I have updated to the latest available Home Assistant version.
- [X] I have cleared the cache of my browser.
- [X] I have tried a different browser to see if it is related to my browser.

### Describe the issue you are experiencing

After selecting gear icon for any entity, the option to change the unit of measurement is missing in Core 2023.11.0b0 beta
It is present in previous versions.

![CleanShot 2023-10-26 at 12 52 47@2x](https://github.com/home-assistant/frontend/assets/2456810/4b1fc343-885a-4bda-8dcc-aff3d03ed7fc)


### Describe the behavior you expected

Core Version 2023.9.3

![CleanShot 2023-10-26 at 12 51 55@2x](https://github.com/home-assistant/frontend/assets/2456810/e9fc52e5-df6e-4217-9af0-d6ee8a9ac05f)


### Steps to reproduce the issue

1. Choose existing entity from within HA
2. Click gear option



### What version of Home Assistant Core has the issue?

core-2023.11.0b0

### What was the last working version of Home Assistant Core?

core-2023.10.x

### In which browser are you experiencing the issue with?

Chrome 118.0.5993.117, Firefox 119.0

### Which operating system are you using to run this browser?

macOS Sonoma 14.1

issue.title: Dashboards fail to load in iOS 15 (2023.11.0b0)
issue.body:
### Checklist

- [X] I have updated to the latest available Home Assistant version.
- [X] I have cleared the cache of my browser.
- [X] I have tried a different browser to see if it is related to my browser.

### Describe the issue you are experiencing

After updating to 2023.11.0b0, I found that dashboards don't load when accessing Home Assistant with Safari(iOS 15.1) or the Home Assistant companion app (I'm assuming this is due to it also using webkit). The following is seen when either accessing Home Assistant via Mobile Safari or the iOS companion app:

![IMG_6627DFC1A169-1](https://github.com/home-assistant/frontend/assets/52541649/16fb70d8-c2c7-4f7e-8fa6-442a1c837eca)


I can confirm that this doesn't affect any other browsers (including more up to date Mac and iOS devices).
I have included an output from the dev console showing errors encountered on the iOS device.

### Describe the behavior you expected

Dashboards should load normally.

### Steps to reproduce the issue

Connect to Home Assistant on an iOS device running iOS 15.


### What version of Home Assistant Core has the issue?

2023.11.0b0

### What was the last working version of Home Assistant Core?

2023.10.5

### In which browser are you experiencing the issue with?

iOS Safari

### Which operating system are you using to run this browser?

iOS 15.1

### State of relevant entities

_No response_

_No response_

### Javascript errors shown in your browser console/inspector

```txt

```
```

parseModule
(anonymous function)
asyncFunctionResume
(anonymous function)
promiseReactionJobWithoutPromise
	(anonymous function) (app-wENyGOpR21s.js:2:88631)
	promiseReactionJob
```

issue.title: "AQI" & "pH" device classes: cannot specify "" uom
issue.body:
### The problem

Consider this template sensor:
```
template:
  - sensor:
      - name: testing_device_class_aqi
        device_class: aqi
        state: >-
          {% set INPUT_NAME = "input_number.testing_device_class_aqi" -%}
          {{ states(INPUT_NAME) }}
```
and then this history-graph:
![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/71872483/c2ca8a8f-bf56-4c85-a81a-d3586429fe49)

If uom is added:
```
      - name: testing_device_class_aqi
        device_class: aqi
        unit_of_measurement: ""
        state: >-
          {% set INPUT_NAME = "input_number.testing_device_class_aqi" -%}
          {{ states(INPUT_NAME) }}
```
then the graph is correct:
![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/71872483/d7989707-ff84-45d0-9606-944f344a23b1)
But there is an error in Log:
2023-09-29 19:14:30.179 WARNING (MainThread) [homeassistant.components.sensor] Entity sensor.testing_device_class_aqi (<class 'homeassistant.components.template.sensor.SensorTemplate'>) is using native unit of measurement '' which is not a valid unit for the device class ('aqi') it is using; expected one of ['no unit of measurement']; Please update your configuration if your entity is manually configured, otherwise create a bug report at https://github.com/home-assistant/core/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22integration%3A+template%22

The same is for the `pH` device_class.

### What version of Home Assistant Core has the issue?

2023.9.3

### What was the last working version of Home Assistant Core?

_No response_

### What type of installation are you running?

Home Assistant Container

issue.body:
### The problem

Consider this template sensor:
```
template:
  - sensor:
      - name: testing_device_class_aqi
        device_class: aqi
        state: >-
          {% set INPUT_NAME = "input_number.testing_device_class_aqi" -%}
          {{ states(INPUT_NAME) }}
```
and then this history-graph:
![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/71872483/c2ca8a8f-bf56-4c85-a81a-d3586429fe49)

If uom is added:
```
      - name: testing_device_class_aqi
        device_class: aqi
        unit_of_measurement: ""
        state: >-
          {% set INPUT_NAME = "input_number.testing_device_class_aqi" -%}
          {{ states(INPUT_NAME) }}
```
then the graph is correct:
![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/71872483/d7989707-ff84-45d0-9606-944f344a23b1)
But there is an error in Log:
2023-09-29 19:14:30.179 WARNING (MainThread) [homeassistant.components.sensor] Entity sensor.testing_device_class_aqi (<class 'homeassistant.components.template.sensor.SensorTemplate'>) is using native unit of measurement '' which is not a valid unit for the device class ('aqi') it is using; expected one of ['no unit of measurement']; Please update your configuration if your entity is manually configured, otherwise create a bug report at https://github.com/home-assistant/core/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22integration%3A+template%22

The same is for the `pH` device_class.

### What version of Home Assistant Core has the issue?

2023.9.3
